</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/uqandail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qandail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(8/6/01 7:31:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shield of Aegis</span><hr size=1> The Shield is Called the &quot;Aegis of Life&quot;.  In order to obtain it, you must do several things.<br>
<br>
1.  Kill Lord Grimrot (Live version).  He is level 40 or so Paladin and can deal alot of Damage.  Would not recommend a Cleric try to solo him.  Highly magic Resistant.  Drops Scythe of Petulence(?).<br>
<br>
2.  Kill Lord Grimrot (Dead version).  He is about level 30-35.  Can easily be soloed by a 52 Cleric.  The version had a pet.  Drops Heart.<br>
<br>
Spawn time on the place holder is 3 hours 20 minutes in RL.  PH is the only Putrid Skeleton the remains standing.<br>
<br>
3.  Need to con warmly or higher.  To obtain this faction, kill all of the putrid skeletons at the undead camp while waiting for Grinrot to spawn.  This builds faction with Priest of Life.<br>
Collect all Bone chips that drop.  Give to Lashun Novashine in Qeynos, 2 at a time, this also builds faction.  If all else fails, give Lashun Novashine 2gp to raise factions.<br>
<br>
Hope this info helps a fellow Cleric.  If you wish to discuss it further, give me a tell.<br>
<br>
Qandail Inthewind<br>
Cleric of the 53rd Band-aid<br>
